<DetailLayout
  title="Mountain and River Scroll"
  src="https://sketchfab.com/models/dd37769bdc0148a988535f893d01c551/embed?autostart=1&dnt=1"
>
  <p class="description">
    This model is inspired by <em>A Thousand Li of Rivers and Mountains</em>, a celebrated landscape scroll painted by Wang Ximeng during the Northern Song Dynasty (960–1127). I like the vibe of the reproduction — the layered mountains and the handwriting drifting through the background. Worth noting: the mountains here don't follow the exact positions of the original, and the model captures only a tenth of the scroll's full length. As for the calligraphy, I know it's a tough task to reproduce it in the model — a purist would have a few words to say — but the spirit is there. Check out more details from the <a class="ext-link" href="https://www.dpm.org.cn/collection/paint/228354.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Palace Museum</a>.
  </p>
</DetailLayout>

